- Uh-huh. Go on.

465
00:33:58,769 --> 00:34:03,331
Hey. There's some things
I can talk about and there's
some things I can't talk about.

466
00:34:03,407 --> 00:34:07,639
And there's some things I won't
talk about, because I don't like
you lawyers twisting the truth,

467
00:34:07,711 --> 00:34:11,272
getting killers off
on some legal technicality.

468
00:34:11,348 --> 00:34:16,285
That's bullshit. Besides,
it's too late for new information, kid.

469
00:34:16,353 --> 00:34:19,186
The courts won't hear it.
You know that.

470
00:34:19,256 --> 00:34:22,191
The courts don't have
the final say in this case.

471
00:34:22,259 --> 00:34:26,491
Besides, you say he wasn't
involved in the nasty stuff.
There's no way he meant to kill.

472
00:34:26,563 --> 00:34:29,191
Of course he meant to kill.

473
00:34:29,266 --> 00:34:32,201
Marvin Kramer was
a creature of habit.

474
00:34:32,269 --> 00:34:35,727
He was in that office
every morning before 8:00.

475
00:34:35,806 --> 00:34:38,400
The bomb went off
straight up at 8:00.

476
00:34:38,475 --> 00:34:40,409
The timer was set for 8:00.

477
00:34:41,611 --> 00:34:43,545
That was never introduced
at trial.

478
00:34:43,613 --> 00:34:47,310
Hey, I can't help it if the damn
lawyers didn't make use of it.
It was in our report.

479
00:34:48,485 --> 00:34:50,578
Well, I'd like to see
that report.

480
00:34:50,654 --> 00:34:54,317
Well, I can't help you there.
I'm just a fisherman now,

481
00:34:54,391 --> 00:34:56,416
who'd just as soon see him gassed.

482
00:34:57,828 --> 00:35:01,229
I've been around those
violent assholes all my life.

483
00:35:01,298 --> 00:35:03,994
Let them taste the other end
of violence.

484
00:35:04,067 --> 00:35:07,093
See how brave they are
without their hoods.

485
00:35:08,672 --> 00:35:10,936
You know what
I'm talking about.

486
00:35:14,845 --> 00:35:18,508
Why would our F.B.I. friend
not wanna tell us something
about a 30-year-old case?

487
00:35:18,582 --> 00:35:21,574
'Cause you're in Mississippi now.
Land of the secrets.

488
00:35:21,651 --> 00:35:24,313
There are bodies buried everywhere.

489
00:35:24,388 --> 00:35:28,415
But no one's trying to hide
anything about Sam. They
don't have to. He did it.

490
00:35:28,492 --> 00:35:31,325
They just don't want you
sifting through the ashes,

491
00:35:31,395 --> 00:35:33,556
'cause they're not sure
what else you might turn up.

492
00:35:33,630 --> 00:35:36,724
- Who is they?
- Everyone.

493
00:35:36,800 --> 00:35:38,734
No one. What difference does it make?

494
00:35:38,802 --> 00:35:43,398
Well, maybe a lot.
I mean, take you, for instance.

495
00:35:43,473 --> 00:35:46,101
Are you really here
to help me?

496
00:35:46,176 --> 00:35:48,736
Or did they assign you
to spy on me?

497
00:35:55,218 --> 00:35:57,209
You ever heard
of the Sovereignty Commission?

498
00:35:57,287 --> 00:36:01,314
- Vaguely.
- Well, it doesn't exist anymore.

499
00:36:01,391 --> 00:36:05,623
They started it in the '50s.
It was an official state agency
dedicated to states' rights,

500
00:36:05,695 --> 00:36:08,186
i.e., fighting civil rights.

501
00:36:08,265 --> 00:36:11,598
Some people think it was
actually coordinating all
of the white citizens' councils.

502
00:36:11,668 --> 00:36:14,296
- What were those?
- Every town had one.

503
00:36:14,371 --> 00:36:17,670
A local group
of respectable white people...

504
00:36:17,741 --> 00:36:21,609
professional types,
pillars of their community...

505
00:36:21,678 --> 00:36:23,612
who told the Klan what to do.

506
00:36:25,382 --> 00:36:27,907
So somebody like Sam
wasn't even making decisions.

507
00:36:27,984 --> 00:36:31,215
[Scoffs]
Like our F.B.I. friend said,

508
00:36:31,288 --> 00:36:36,191
they were poor, uneducated bigots who
couldn't find their butts with a map.

509
00:36:36,259 --> 00:36:40,593
- The citizens' councils used them
to do their dirty work.
- And the Sovereignty Commission?

510
00:36:40,664 --> 00:36:43,531
They kept the records.

511
00:36:45,602 --> 00:36:48,503
- Sam, please sign this.
- I ain't signin' nothin'.

512
00:36:48,572 --> 00:36:51,473
The files are sealed
by the state legislature;
as a defendant on death row,

513
00:36:51,541 --> 00:36:53,805
you and only you can apply
to have your files opened.

514
00:36:55,045 --> 00:36:57,479
You're set to die in 20 days.
This might help.

515
00:36:57,547 --> 00:37:00,812
- Help him, maybe. Not me.
- Help who?

516
00:37:00,884 --> 00:37:03,580
The governor, you dumb ass.
Can't you see it?

517
00:37:03,653 --> 00:37:06,554
He can't open the files hisself,
so he gets you to do it for him.

518
00:37:06,623 --> 00:37:08,853
Why? To help me?
[Scoffs]

519
00:37:08,925 --> 00:37:13,055
He put me here. Nah. He's just fishin'
for what every politician wants:

520
00:37:13,129 --> 00:37:16,030
dirt on their enemies.

521
00:37:16,099 --> 00:37:19,227
What's in those files, Sam?

522
00:37:19,302 --> 00:37:23,363
Nothin' for you. No, it's just
stuff they'd use to twist around
and hurt my people.

523
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:25,567
I'm your people.

524
00:37:25,642 --> 00:37:28,338
Don't you get it? I am.

525
00:37:28,411 --> 00:37:31,972
You ain't my real people.
You ain't never met my real people.

526
00:37:35,252 --> 00:37:38,153
I don't know how
they got the story.

527
00:37:38,221 --> 00:37:41,088
[Lee On Phone]
It's only a matter of time
before they get around to me.

528
00:37:41,157 --> 00:37:45,856
I am sorry. But I might be
onto something. I'm following
some leads from way back.

529
00:37:45,929 --> 00:37:48,261
For God's sake, Adam.
Leave it alone.

530
00:37:48,331 --> 00:37:50,697
Lee, I really think
I can save him.

531
00:37:52,502 --> 00:37:55,027
Ever occur to you
he might not be worth savin'?

532
00:37:55,105 --> 00:37:58,836
- You can't mean that.
- All right, Adam.

533
00:37:58,909 --> 00:38:02,504
You wanna know about the past?

534
00:38:02,579 --> 00:38:05,241
I'll tell you about the past.

535
00:39:17,787 --> 00:39:19,982
[Lee] This was my tree.

536
00:39:26,896 --> 00:39:29,057
My own...

537
00:39:29,132 --> 00:39:31,066
laurel tree.

538
00:39:33,536 --> 00:39:36,596
I was up there.

539
00:39:41,344 --> 00:39:44,609
Your father was there,
with Quince.

540
00:39:46,783 --> 00:39:48,717
They were eight.
Maybe they were nine.

541
00:39:48,785 --> 00:39:50,719
And they were best friends.

542
00:39:56,626 --> 00:40:00,187
They were fightin' and kickin', and
they made so much noise Daddy heard...

543
00:40:00,263 --> 00:40:03,027
and come out to see
what all the ruckus was.

544
00:40:03,099 --> 00:40:05,567
You hear me? Go on. Go on.

545
00:40:05,635 --> 00:40:07,569
Get on home!

546
00:40:07,637 --> 00:40:10,765
Quince's father did day work
for Daddy.

547
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:15,106
His name was Joe. Daddy never was
very handy at mechanical things,

548
00:40:15,178 --> 00:40:17,874
so Joe fixed things for us;
he made things.

549
00:40:17,947 --> 00:40:20,711
H-He was here, all the time.

550
00:40:20,784 --> 00:40:25,221
So then Quince came back
with his father.

551
00:40:25,288 --> 00:40:28,052
[Joe] My boy, Quince,
said you been beatin' on him.

552
00:40:28,124 --> 00:40:30,558
[Lee] They fought so hard.
Like animals.

553
00:40:30,627 --> 00:40:34,757
At one point,
Daddy grabbed the rake.

554
00:40:34,831 --> 00:40:36,765
And things got out of hand.

555
00:40:38,935 --> 00:40:41,495
He knocked Joe over.
Joe fell to the ground.

556
00:40:41,571 --> 00:40:43,937
And he yelled for Quince
to run get his shotgun.

557
00:40:44,007 --> 00:40:45,634
Go get my shotgun!

558
00:40:45,709 --> 00:40:49,201
Sam told Eddie to go get his.
Eddie froze.

559
00:40:49,279 --> 00:40:51,270
But Daddy made him go.

560
00:40:52,749 --> 00:40:56,207
Joe... was here.

561
00:40:57,353 --> 00:40:59,287
Daddy was there.

562
00:40:59,355 --> 00:41:03,451
- Get in the house. Go on.
- [Lee] Joe waited for his gun.

563
00:41:03,526 --> 00:41:05,761
H-He kept lookin' around.

564
00:41:05,894 --> 00:41:08,590
Sam had his.

565
00:41:08,663 --> 00:41:12,394
And then my dear,
sweet father...

566
00:41:13,668 --> 00:41:16,102
[Gasps]

567
00:41:17,572 --> 00:41:19,506
[Exhales]

568
00:41:30,152 --> 00:41:33,019
[Laughs Softly]

569
00:41:34,756 --> 00:41:36,690
This...

570
00:41:36,758 --> 00:41:39,488
was Mississippi...

571
00:41:39,561 --> 00:41:41,859
in the early '50s.

572
00:41:44,299 --> 00:41:46,460
Daddy said self-defense.

573
00:41:46,535 --> 00:41:50,596
He was never even
so much as arrested.

574
00:41:50,672 --> 00:41:53,641
What were my dad a-and Quince
fightin' about?

575
00:41:59,848 --> 00:42:01,782
A toy soldier.

576
00:42:01,850 --> 00:42:05,308
Eddie thought Quince had stolen it.

577
00:42:05,387 --> 00:42:07,514
That night he found it
under his bed.

578
00:42:09,291 --> 00:42:13,159
He took the weight of the world
on his shoulders.

579
00:42:13,228 --> 00:42:15,788
And then he said...

580
00:42:15,864 --> 00:42:18,628
I...

581
00:42:18,700 --> 00:42:21,601
had killed Joe Lincoln too.

582
00:42:26,708 --> 00:42:30,269
He said if I had cried out
for Daddy to stop,

583
00:42:31,947 --> 00:42:35,246
no way would he have fired.

584
00:42:35,317 --> 00:42:38,252
Not with his sweet baby girl watchin'.

585
00:42:42,424 --> 00:42:44,358
Of course he was right.

586
00:42:48,763 --> 00:42:51,231
[Crying] It was my fault too.

587
00:42:57,005 --> 00:42:58,939
[Sobbing]

588
00:43:04,512 --> 00:43:08,471
[Eddie's Voice] It's mine!

589
00:43:08,550 --> 00:43:11,075
[Sam's Voice] Get on home!

590
00:43:11,152 --> 00:43:13,382
[Joe's Voice] Quince! Quince!

591
00:43:16,992 --> 00:43:18,926
[Joe Grunting In Pain]

592
00:43:18,994 --> 00:43:21,519
[Exhales]

593
00:43:21,596 --> 00:43:23,530
[Joe's Voice] Help me, Quince.

594
00:43:23,598 --> 00:43:26,260
[Sam's Voice] Get my shotgun!

595
00:43:31,139 --> 00:43:35,269
[Lee's Voice] Daddy wasn't
very handy with mechanical things.

596
00:43:36,344 --> 00:43:38,778
Jesus!

597
00:43:38,847 --> 00:43:41,645
- [Alarm Buzzing]
- [Prison Gate Buzzing]

598
00:43:41,716 --> 00:43:45,618
The superintendent asked if you've
been thinkin' about your last meal.

599
00:43:45,687 --> 00:43:49,885
- Mmm.
- Special requests can take time.

600
00:43:49,958 --> 00:43:52,392
Yeah, I want, uh...

601
00:43:52,460 --> 00:43:55,918
a bowl of Eskimo Pies
and French Market coffee.

602
00:43:55,997 --> 00:43:58,431
It shall be done.

603
00:43:58,500 --> 00:44:00,695
There's been five executions
since you been here, Sam.

604
00:44:00,769 --> 00:44:02,703
You know anything
about any problems with any of 'em?

605
00:44:02,771 --> 00:44:05,137
Come on.

606
00:44:05,206 --> 00:44:08,403
They all died
within 50 feet of me.

607
00:44:08,476 --> 00:44:11,240
Everybody on the row knows everything
about every killin'.

608
00:44:11,313 --> 00:44:14,476
Tell me about Teddy Meeks, then.
I want to hear every detail.

609
00:44:16,851 --> 00:44:19,547
They didn't know
what they were doin'.

610
00:44:19,621 --> 00:44:22,215
Everything went wrong.

611
00:44:22,290 --> 00:44:24,224
Have you seen the chamber?

612
00:44:24,292 --> 00:44:27,921
- Not yet.
- Well, there's a little room
off to one side...

613
00:44:27,996 --> 00:44:32,456
where the executioner goes to mix
up his solution of sulfuric acid.

614
00:44:32,534 --> 00:44:35,935
With Meeks,
the executioner was drunk.

615
00:44:36,004 --> 00:44:38,768
- Come on.
- He was drunk.

616
00:44:40,508 --> 00:44:43,944
Anyway. [Sighs]

617
00:44:45,013 --> 00:44:48,210
His first batch of brew didn't work.

618
00:44:48,283 --> 00:44:51,446
And Meeks held his breath
for as long as he could.

619
00:44:51,519 --> 00:44:53,783
Then he inhaled
and nothin' happened.

620
00:44:53,855 --> 00:44:56,050
So they waited.

621
00:44:56,124 --> 00:44:58,524
Meeks waited.
The witnesses waited.

622
00:44:58,593 --> 00:45:01,619
And slowly, they turned
toward the executioner,

623
00:45:01,696 --> 00:45:03,630
who's waitin' and cussin'.

624
00:45:03,698 --> 00:45:05,791
He finally goes back
to his little room;

625
00:45:05,867 --> 00:45:09,303
he mixes up another batch
of sulfuric acid and pulls the lever.

626
00:45:09,371 --> 00:45:11,999
This time the sulfuric acid drops
down where it's supposed to.

627
00:45:12,073 --> 00:45:14,803
Pulls the second lever,

628
00:45:14,876 --> 00:45:16,810
droppin' the cyanide pellets.

629
00:45:16,878 --> 00:45:21,372
Sure enough, this gas
starts driftin' upward...

630
00:45:21,449 --> 00:45:25,886
to where old Teddy is holdin'
his breath again. [Chuckles]

631
00:45:28,490 --> 00:45:32,324
So finally he sucks in
a whole nose full of it...

632
00:45:32,394 --> 00:45:35,124
and starts shakin' and jerkin'.

633
00:45:35,196 --> 00:45:40,133
Well, somewhere or another
there's a... a metal pole...

634
00:45:40,201 --> 00:45:42,601
that runs from the top
of the chamber down to the bottom,

635
00:45:42,670 --> 00:45:45,571
and it's right directly
behind the... the chair.

636
00:45:45,640 --> 00:45:48,074
And...

637
00:45:48,143 --> 00:45:50,077
[Exhales]

638
00:45:54,416 --> 00:45:57,613
And just about the time
Meeks got real still...

639
00:45:57,685 --> 00:46:00,017
and everybody thought he was dead,

640
00:46:00,088 --> 00:46:03,182
his head starts bangin'
back and forth against that pole.

641
00:46:03,258 --> 00:46:07,524
Just beatin' the hell
out of it like that.

642
00:46:07,595 --> 00:46:11,622
His eyes rolled up in his head,
and his lips opened up real wide.

643
00:46:11,699 --> 00:46:14,691
And he was foamin' at the mouth.

644
00:46:14,769 --> 00:46:16,703
And there he was,

645
00:46:18,273 --> 00:46:21,765
just bangin' the back
of his head against that pole.

646
00:46:24,846 --> 00:46:26,780
It was sick.

647
00:46:28,383 --> 00:46:30,351
How long did it take them
to kill him?

648
00:46:30,418 --> 00:46:34,980
According to the prison doctor,
death was instant and painless.

649
00:46:35,056 --> 00:46:39,049
Packer told me it was
the longest five minutes of his life.

650
00:46:39,127 --> 00:46:42,790
The guy convulsed and heaved...

651
00:46:42,864 --> 00:46:44,798
and pounded his skull for so long...

652
00:46:44,866 --> 00:46:48,267
that pieces of his brain was
flyin' out the top of his head.

653
00:47:03,017 --> 00:47:05,383
How does this lever they pull
activate the cyanide canister?

654
00:47:07,088 --> 00:47:09,921
- What?
- The lever. Does it work
with hinges or springs?

655
00:47:09,991 --> 00:47:13,154
- I don't know.
- Well, is it just gravity
that's forcing it down?

656
00:47:13,228 --> 00:47:15,219
Well, how in the hell
would I know that?

657
00:47:15,296 --> 00:47:17,787
Just thought you had an aptitude
for this sort of thing.

658
00:47:17,866 --> 00:47:21,632
Well, sue me.
I'm not mechanical.

659
00:47:21,703 --> 00:47:24,171
That's what Lee said.

660
00:47:24,239 --> 00:47:27,037
But you were handy enough to build
a bomb to kill the Kramer twins.

661
00:47:27,108 --> 00:47:29,804
Son of a bitch.
Is that what this is all about?

662
00:47:29,878 --> 00:47:33,746
[Chuckles] You must've stayed up
all night thinking of this one.

663
00:47:33,815 --> 00:47:37,251
Sorry, bubba.
I hate to disappoint you,

664
00:47:37,318 --> 00:47:41,277
- But, uh, bombs ain't
that complicated.
- They couldn't be that easy.

665
00:47:41,356 --> 00:47:45,349
- I wouldn't know how to do it.
- That's 'cause you're not motivated.

666
00:47:45,426 --> 00:47:48,418
By the time I did Kramer,
I had it down real simple.

667
00:47:48,496 --> 00:47:50,987
So just because you're
an anti-Semite,

668
00:47:51,065 --> 00:47:54,057
you know how to build a bomb,
strategically place it
on the second story,

669
00:47:54,135 --> 00:47:56,194
light a fuse, and then get out
of there without any risk to yourself.

670
00:47:56,271 --> 00:47:59,468
Plenty of risk.
Not much glory.

671
00:47:59,541 --> 00:48:04,308
And it was the first floor.
The bomb went off below 'em.
Check the F.B.I. report.

672
00:48:04,379 --> 00:48:06,472
- I did.
- What did it say?

673
00:48:06,548 --> 00:48:09,949
Bomb went off below 'em.

674
00:48:10,018 --> 00:48:12,782
Thank you very much.
Anything else I can help you with?

675
00:48:12,854 --> 00:48:16,051
- How long was the fuse?
- For Pete's sake.

676
00:48:16,124 --> 00:48:19,150
You know, it happened a long time ago.
l-I'm an old man.

677
00:48:19,227 --> 00:48:21,695
My memory isn't that perfect.
Get off my back, here. Will you?

678
00:48:21,763 --> 00:48:23,856
Oh, I'm sure you can remember
killing two little children.

679
00:48:23,932 --> 00:48:27,834
Long enough for me to get
the hell out of there. Okay?

680
00:48:27,902 --> 00:48:32,532
Except for one thing. The bomb
didn't have a fuse. It had a timer.

681
00:48:32,607 --> 00:48:37,408
- What are you sayin'?
- I'm sayin' you weren't alone.
There was somebody else.

682
00:48:37,478 --> 00:48:41,107
There's not a chance in hell you could
have built a timing device by yourself.

683
00:48:41,182 --> 00:48:43,673
The F.B.I., they searched
your house, your... your garage.

684
00:48:43,751 --> 00:48:47,619
They didn't find a single trace
of explosives anywhere.

685
00:48:47,689 --> 00:48:50,487
Well, maybe they're stupid.

686
00:48:50,558 --> 00:48:53,425
Maybe I was just real careful
and didn't leave a trail.

687
00:48:54,696 --> 00:48:56,664
Yeah. And maybe someone else
planted the bomb.

688
00:48:56,731 --> 00:48:59,495
[Explosion]

689
00:49:03,605 --> 00:49:05,539
You have no idea
what you're doin'.

690
00:49:09,244 --> 00:49:12,077
Just hear me out.
Sam couldn't construct a timer.

691
00:49:12,146 --> 00:49:14,410
His bombs were crude.
They had fuses.

692
00:49:14,482 --> 00:49:16,712
This one was different.
It was complex.

693
00:49:16,784 --> 00:49:19,878
- L-lt was timed.
It was timed to kill.
- Okay. Wait a minute.

694
00:49:19,954 --> 00:49:22,787
Sam did not plant that bomb.
He did not kill those kids.

695
00:49:22,857 --> 00:49:25,261
Wait!

696
00:49:27,730 --> 00:49:32,565
The Sovereignty Commission
has a file on Sam.
It might tell who else was involved!

697
00:49:32,635 --> 00:49:34,569
Adam, just stop this. Okay?

698
00:49:34,637 --> 00:49:36,832
Those files are sealed
by the state legislature.

699
00:49:36,905 --> 00:49:40,204
If your client won't sign, you cannot
move the court to unseal them.

700
00:49:40,276 --> 00:49:42,938
- I bet you know a way
we could take a peek at 'em.
- No.

701
00:49:43,012 --> 00:49:45,412
- You said you wanted to help me.
- I am.

702
00:49:45,481 --> 00:49:47,779
- Maybe you need to do more.
- Maybe I can't do more.

703
00:49:47,850 --> 00:49:52,219
Nora, if there's others,
and you're involved in protecting them...

704
00:49:52,288 --> 00:49:55,052
l...

705
00:49:55,124 --> 00:49:57,058
Are you threatening me?

706
00:49:57,126 --> 00:49:59,788
I am pursuing the truth
by any means necessary!

707
00:50:05,434 --> 00:50:09,063
Which includes...
politely asking for your help.

708
00:50:12,608 --> 00:50:14,542
[Sighs]

709
00:50:16,478 --> 00:50:19,276
In addition to appealing cruel
and unusual, I wanna file a new motion.

710
00:50:19,348 --> 00:50:21,612
About time you focused
on the law, bubba.

711
00:50:21,684 --> 00:50:24,312
I never stopped focusing
on the law, bubba!

712
00:50:24,386 --> 00:50:26,854
But there is nothing that I will not
pursue in order to get a stay,

713
00:50:26,922 --> 00:50:28,856
including proving
that you're insane.

714
00:50:28,924 --> 00:50:31,392
- I'm insane?
- That's right.

715
00:50:31,460 --> 00:50:34,520
I'm gonna argue that as a product
of three generations of Klan mentality,

716
00:50:34,596 --> 00:50:38,930
your preconscious indoctrination
into hate and distortion
born of irrational fear...

717
00:50:39,001 --> 00:50:41,868
has resulted in diminished mental
capacity to determine right from wrong.

718
00:50:41,937 --> 00:50:46,465
You're gonna argue I'm insane because
I held different political beliefs...

719
00:50:46,542 --> 00:50:49,170
than you and your father...

720
00:50:49,244 --> 00:50:52,771
in his naive, nigger-lovin',
bleedin'-heart bullshit!

721
00:50:52,848 --> 00:50:56,682
Well, I probably won't use
those exact words in my brief.

722
00:50:56,752 --> 00:50:59,277
I'll just wait and see
the psychiatrist's report.

723
00:50:59,355 --> 00:51:02,449
- Oh, I'm gonna see a psychiatrist, am I?
- That's right.

724
00:51:02,524 --> 00:51:04,492
Mmm. That's insane.

725
00:51:04,560 --> 00:51:08,189
Killing two five-year-olds
'cause their father was working
for civil rights is insane.

726
00:51:09,598 --> 00:51:11,532
Never meant to kill those kids.

727
00:51:11,600 --> 00:51:13,534
[Scoffs] That's fine.
But it just happens to be the crime...

728
00:51:13,602 --> 00:51:16,537
which you're to be executed
for in exactly 14 days.

729
00:51:22,144 --> 00:51:24,078
Okay.

730
00:51:25,080 --> 00:51:27,014
Good.

731
00:51:28,484 --> 00:51:32,011
I need to go over some more
family background with you.

732
00:51:32,087 --> 00:51:35,818
I got some stuff from Lee,
but there's a lot of holes in it.

733
00:51:53,075 --> 00:51:55,771
She's going through
a tough time right now.

734
00:51:55,844 --> 00:51:59,041
I tried to call her when I saw this,
but she didn't answer.

735
00:52:03,252 --> 00:52:06,449
I think she's drinking again.

736
00:52:07,823 --> 00:52:10,348
Did you know she's an alcoholic?

737
00:52:16,632 --> 00:52:20,932
Have you ever felt feelings
of remorse for any of your crimes?

738
00:52:21,003 --> 00:52:22,937
No.

739
00:52:24,606 --> 00:52:28,337
Have you ever apologized
to your victim's family?

740
00:52:30,679 --> 00:52:32,613
No, what would be the point?

741
00:52:34,383 --> 00:52:36,317
What do you think would be the point?

742
00:52:38,520 --> 00:52:40,454
No point.

743
00:52:42,925 --> 00:52:45,359
[Gate Unlocking, Sliding]

744
00:53:07,850 --> 00:53:10,614
Packer.

745
00:53:10,686 --> 00:53:15,055
I want you to know that
when I talk about your people,

746
00:53:15,123 --> 00:53:17,421
l...

747
00:53:17,493 --> 00:53:19,427
Well...

748
00:53:21,196 --> 00:53:23,130
I hear you, Sam.

749
00:53:37,145 --> 00:53:39,079
[Door Locking]

750
00:54:43,345 --> 00:54:45,279
[Adam] In your professional opinion,
then, does Sam Cayhall...

751
00:54:45,347 --> 00:54:48,248
have anything that might even remotely
be called a conscience?

752
00:54:48,317 --> 00:54:50,785
I found no evidence of one.

753
00:54:50,852 --> 00:54:54,344
Dr. Biddows, in your opinion,
is Sam Cayhall in touch with reality?

754
00:54:54,423 --> 00:54:58,382
- No, he is not.
- Thank you, Dr. Biddows.

755
00:54:58,460 --> 00:55:01,190
No further questions,
Your Honor.

756
00:55:02,364 --> 00:55:04,264
What saith the state?

757
00:55:04,333 --> 00:55:06,733
The state calls
Sergeant Clyde Packer.

758
00:55:10,038 --> 00:55:13,565
Sergeant, would you inform
this court how long...

759
00:55:13,642 --> 00:55:16,008
you have held
your present position, please?

760
00:55:16,078 --> 00:55:20,276
Been running the row for 15 years, sir,
and Sam's been with me the whole time.

761
00:55:20,349 --> 00:55:23,785
And during this time
have you ever observed Mr. Cayhall...

762
00:55:23,852 --> 00:55:25,911
demonstrate he might have a conscience?

763
00:55:25,988 --> 00:55:29,151
Cared about other people's feelings?

764
00:55:29,224 --> 00:55:34,093
Oh, yes, sir. Everybody knows
that Sam has a real bad attitude
toward black folk.

765
00:55:34,162 --> 00:55:38,223
But just the other night he told me to
my face when he says stuff like that...

766
00:55:38,300 --> 00:55:42,066
Let's just say he tried to apologize.
And he didn't even get it all out.

767
00:55:42,137 --> 00:55:46,904
And it sure don't make him no saint.
But, for Sam, that's a big deal.

768
00:55:46,975 --> 00:55:49,944
He most certainly do has
a conscience. Yes, sir.

769
00:55:50,012 --> 00:55:53,413
And during all this time that
you been observin' Mr. Cayhall,

770
00:55:53,482 --> 00:55:58,249
would you say he knows
what's goin' on around him?

771
00:55:58,320 --> 00:56:01,153
Would you say he's out of,
uh, touch with reality?

772
00:56:03,091 --> 00:56:06,060
A couple of nights back, I was
walkin' past, and he said, Clyde.

773
00:56:06,128 --> 00:56:09,461
He never called me that before,
so I knew it was important.

774
00:56:09,531 --> 00:56:11,863
Could I help?
With what, Sam?

775
00:56:11,933 --> 00:56:16,700
And he said, I wanna die alone.
And I wanna die in decent clothes.

776
00:56:16,772 --> 00:56:19,605
And I wanna eat an Eskimo Pie.

777
00:56:19,675 --> 00:56:21,768
And could I see a sunrise?

778
00:56:21,843 --> 00:56:25,438
I said, Last one's on me, Sam.

779
00:56:25,514 --> 00:56:29,644
So I snuck him out,
gave him a hour alone.

780
00:56:29,718 --> 00:56:33,950
I watched through the inside.
I thought he might lose it
once the sun started comin'.

781
00:56:34,022 --> 00:56:37,150
See, it's been 15 or 16 years...

782
00:56:37,225 --> 00:56:39,159
since Sam last saw dawn break.

783
00:56:39,227 --> 00:56:41,855
But he held together just fine.

784
00:56:41,930 --> 00:56:44,956
[Attorney] In your opinion,
based on your observations,

785
00:56:45,033 --> 00:56:48,161
is Sam Cayhall in touch
with reality?

786
00:56:48,236 --> 00:56:50,636
Sam? You betcha.

787
00:56:50,706 --> 00:56:52,833
Thank you, Sergeant Packer.

788
00:56:52,908 --> 00:56:56,309
- Thank you.
- Tender the witness, Your Honor.

789
00:56:59,281 --> 00:57:01,511
[McAllister] What's happenin'
in the fifth circuit?

790
00:57:01,583 --> 00:57:04,882
- Thumbs down on insanity later today.
- Hi.

791
00:57:04,953 --> 00:57:07,922
- Hi.
- There you are.
What's young Mr. Hall been up to?

792
00:57:07,989 --> 00:57:10,890
- No change.
- Try again. What has he been workin' on?

793
00:57:10,959 --> 00:57:14,759
- He's lookin' everywhere
for new information.
- What kind of information?

794
00:57:14,830 --> 00:57:16,764
- Nora?
- Sir?

795
00:57:19,835 --> 00:57:22,895
You're not sleepin' with him,
are you?

796
00:57:22,971 --> 00:57:26,304
- No.
- Then what kind of information?

797
00:57:26,374 --> 00:57:30,572
- Anything, everything. He's desperate.
- Where is he lookin'?

798
00:57:32,280 --> 00:57:34,305
- I don't know.
- Well, find out.

799
00:57:34,382 --> 00:57:37,613
Desperate people are dangerous.

800
00:57:37,686 --> 00:57:41,554
Maybe you ought to be sleepin'
with him. [Chuckles]

801
00:57:45,327 --> 00:57:47,420
- [Knocking]
- Hey.

802
00:57:47,496 --> 00:57:50,398
- Can we talk?
- Sure.

803
00:57:52,166 --> 00:57:54,100
Tammy?

804
00:58:02,610 --> 00:58:04,840
The Sovereignty Commission
files the originals...

805
00:58:04,912 --> 00:58:07,608
under lock and key
in the Hall of Records.

806
00:58:07,715 --> 00:58:10,946
Why can't zoning reports
wait for tomorrow?

807
00:58:11,018 --> 00:58:13,987
- You ask the governor. I like my job.
- Nora.

808
00:58:14,054 --> 00:58:17,148
- Nora, Nora.
- [Phone Hanging Up]

809
00:58:17,224 --> 00:58:19,488
It's you that I'm scared of.

810
00:58:19,560 --> 00:58:22,586
Bink, please.
I've gotta get this done tonight.

811
00:58:22,663 --> 00:58:25,257
I'll lock up for you.

812
00:58:25,332 --> 00:58:27,664
[Sighs]

813
00:58:27,735 --> 00:58:30,602
- [Keys Jingling]
- Our little secret.

814
00:58:30,671 --> 00:58:35,370
- You and me. Have a good evenin'.
- Uh-huh.

815
00:58:56,697 --> 00:58:58,631
This way.

816
00:59:33,567 --> 00:59:35,501
[Sighs]

817
00:59:36,904 --> 00:59:40,203
- [Grunts]
- Shh.

818
00:59:42,276 --> 00:59:44,210
[Grunts]

819
00:59:48,883 --> 00:59:50,817
Sovereignty Commissions.

820
01:00:12,640 --> 01:00:14,870
White Citizen's Council, Indianola.

821
01:00:19,647 --> 01:00:21,638
Go back.

822
01:00:33,227 --> 01:00:35,661
M.K. situation
should be followed through.

823
01:00:35,729 --> 01:00:38,323
- Marvin Kramer.
- Or Martin King.

824
01:00:38,399 --> 01:00:41,630
Law office, March 18.
It's Marvin Kramer.

825
01:00:41,702 --> 01:00:44,637
- When was the bombing?
- April 28.

826
01:00:47,908 --> 01:00:50,672
Action agreed September 2.
I thought you said it was in April.

827
01:00:50,744 --> 01:00:53,304
That's not a date.
That's nine to two.

828
01:00:53,380 --> 01:00:55,314
- Jesus Christ, they took a vote.
- Oh, my God.

829
01:00:55,382 --> 01:00:59,341
- Commission assigned S.C.
- Sam Cayhall. What's R.W.?

830
01:01:01,488 --> 01:01:03,422
You mean, who's R.W.

831
01:01:15,235 --> 01:01:17,499
[Dog Barking]

832
01:01:17,571 --> 01:01:19,505
Hi. Thanks.

833
01:01:21,342 --> 01:01:23,276
[Truck Honking]

834
01:01:27,781 --> 01:01:29,715
Truth time, Sam. Five days.

835
01:01:29,783 --> 01:01:34,482
We're firing everything we have
up to the Supreme Court, but...

836
01:01:34,555 --> 01:01:37,217
I need to know who R.W. is.

837
01:01:42,963 --> 01:01:47,525
Sam. I saw the Commission's files.
You were with someone named R.W.

838
01:01:47,601 --> 01:01:50,126
The two of you were assigned
to bomb the Kramer office.

839
01:01:50,204 --> 01:01:53,230
Assigned by the same people
who took no responsibility
for the death of those kids...

840
01:01:53,307 --> 01:01:56,799
and, as far as I can see, are gonna take
no responsibility for you.

841
01:01:58,479 --> 01:02:02,245
l-I believe you call
these people cowards.

842
01:02:02,316 --> 01:02:05,843
Why in God's name you feel compelled
to protect them is beyond me.

843
01:02:08,722 --> 01:02:10,656
First of all,

844
01:02:11,892 --> 01:02:14,554
you sniveling little
son of a bitch,

845
01:02:14,628 --> 01:02:18,655
if you ever speak to me like
this again, I'll rip your heart
out and shove it up your butt.

846
01:02:18,732 --> 01:02:23,101
Second, if you spent half as much time
learnin' to be a lawyer...

847
01:02:23,170 --> 01:02:26,230
instead of playin' Dick Tracy,

848
01:02:26,306 --> 01:02:29,002
I might stand a chance
of not bein' dead in five days.

849
01:02:30,444 --> 01:02:34,039
As it stands right now,
everything you tried has failed.

850
01:02:35,449 --> 01:02:37,383
You've failed!

851
01:02:37,451 --> 01:02:41,410
Now I have to pay the price.

852
01:02:41,488 --> 01:02:44,423
You're a failure!
Just like your pathetic father was.

853
01:02:44,491 --> 01:02:47,790
That son of a bitch didn't have
the balls to live.

854
01:02:47,861 --> 01:02:50,193
He was a loser and a quitter.

855
01:02:50,264 --> 01:02:52,960
And he just gave his life away.

856
01:02:53,033 --> 01:02:56,264
How dare he?

857
01:02:56,336 --> 01:02:58,270
What right did he have
to do that?

858
01:02:58,338 --> 01:03:01,967
- It wasn't his to give!
I gave it to him!
- [Guard] Hey, hey, Sam!

859
01:03:02,042 --> 01:03:03,976
His mama gave it to him!
It was God's!

860
01:03:04,044 --> 01:03:07,912
- He had no right!
He just gave it away, goddamn it!
- [Guards Shouting]

861
01:03:07,981 --> 01:03:11,815
- You hear me? He gave it away!
- [Guard Shouting]

862
01:03:11,885 --> 01:03:15,480
- Why'd he do that?
- [Packer] Come on.

863
01:03:15,556 --> 01:03:20,493
- [Inmates, Guards Shouting]
- [Heavy Door Slams]

864
01:03:28,068 --> 01:03:32,095
- Hi. Is she home?
- Miss Lee's upstairs restin'.
She can't see you now.

865
01:03:33,907 --> 01:03:35,841
Lee?

866
01:03:37,411 --> 01:03:40,312
Uh, where are you, Lee?

867
01:03:40,380 --> 01:03:42,314
Lee?

868
01:03:43,884 --> 01:03:45,818
Lee?

869
01:03:47,254 --> 01:03:49,848
Lee?

870
01:03:49,923 --> 01:03:52,517
[Exhales]

871
01:03:54,762 --> 01:03:57,492
[Laughing]

872
01:03:57,564 --> 01:03:59,794
Oh, Jesus.

873
01:04:13,447 --> 01:04:16,848
Lucky little nephew.

874
01:04:21,155 --> 01:04:24,181
Did I ever show you...

875
01:04:24,258 --> 01:04:27,523
my favorite old family picture?

876
01:04:29,062 --> 01:04:32,896
[Laughs] Come here.

877
01:04:32,966 --> 01:04:34,900
I'm coming.

878
01:04:36,203 --> 01:04:38,137
Mmm?

879
01:04:39,606 --> 01:04:42,905
I never kept
an actual photo album.

880
01:04:42,976 --> 01:04:47,276
Mostly because I never kept
any actual photos.

881
01:04:47,347 --> 01:04:49,281
Here. Come here.

882
01:04:56,123 --> 01:04:59,581
Here. Now, there.

883
01:04:59,660 --> 01:05:02,652
[Laughs] See?
[Kissing Sounds]

884
01:05:02,729 --> 01:05:05,323
He was a cute little thing,
wasn't he?

885
01:05:07,367 --> 01:05:11,098
The problem is,
he was raised...

886
01:05:11,171 --> 01:05:13,639
to be a monster.

887
01:05:17,811 --> 01:05:20,405
Trained from birth.

888
01:05:25,752 --> 01:05:28,243
We come from a long line...

889
01:05:28,322 --> 01:05:31,450
of hate, Adam.

890
01:05:31,525 --> 01:05:35,393
[Crying, Chuckling]
That's why I drink.

891
01:05:35,462 --> 01:05:37,760
Make it all go away.

892
01:05:37,831 --> 01:05:40,629
[Sobbing] Now you're here.

893
01:05:40,701 --> 01:05:45,297
And it won't go away anymore.

894
01:05:49,710 --> 01:05:52,270
Go home.

895
01:06:07,394 --> 01:06:09,885
I've got three things
to say to you.

896
01:06:09,963 --> 01:06:11,954
Number one.
I'm your lawyer until you fire me.

897
01:06:12,032 --> 01:06:14,193
I'm not quitting.
Number two.

898
01:06:14,267 --> 01:06:18,567
The day you killed Joe Lincoln,
your sweet little seven-year-old
daughter was in the laurel tree.

899
01:06:18,638 --> 01:06:21,903
She watched her daddy murder
a defenseless man in cold blood.

900
01:06:21,975 --> 01:06:24,808
And three.
Quince Lincoln never stole a thing.

901
01:06:24,878 --> 01:06:28,814
My father found that toy soldier
underneath his bed,
but he was too terrified to tell you.

902
01:06:28,882 --> 01:06:32,841
He had to live with that
for the rest of his sad life.

903
01:06:32,919 --> 01:06:37,083
Maybe you didn't have the balls
to put a stop to this, Sam. But I do.

904
01:06:37,157 --> 01:06:41,184
It ends with me.
We got four days left.

905
01:06:41,261 --> 01:06:44,788
This is our last appeal, and it's
called mitigating circumstances.

906
01:06:44,865 --> 01:06:47,595
Talk to me.

907
01:06:48,935 --> 01:06:51,096
Talk to me, Sam!

908
01:06:53,206 --> 01:06:55,140
I'm tired of talkin'.

909
01:06:57,644 --> 01:07:02,479
I'm tired of wakin' up every mornin'
knowin' I'm one day closer to dyin'.

910
01:07:02,549 --> 01:07:06,485
I'm tired of livin' in a cage,
tired of these crappy cigarettes.

911
01:07:06,553 --> 01:07:08,987
[Chuckles] Just prayin' I'll die
of cancer before they...

912
01:07:09,055 --> 01:07:10,989
gas me.

913
01:07:12,359 --> 01:07:16,056
[Sighs]
But mostly I'm just tired of waitin'.

914
01:07:22,736 --> 01:07:24,670
Just let me rest.

915
01:07:24,738 --> 01:07:28,367
I'm really touched you feel close enough
to share your feelings with me, Sam.

916
01:07:28,441 --> 01:07:30,466
But at the moment,
I don't really give a damn.

917
01:07:30,544 --> 01:07:34,503
I'm too busy tryin'
to win my case.

918
01:07:34,581 --> 01:07:37,015
Now, start talking!

919
01:07:38,885 --> 01:07:40,819
Here are some synonyms
for mitigating.

920
01:07:40,887 --> 01:07:44,448
Glossing over, sugarcoating,

921
01:07:44,524 --> 01:07:46,458
prettifying.

922
01:07:46,526 --> 01:07:49,495
There's nothing pretty
about twin boys being blown to bits.

923
01:07:49,563 --> 01:07:52,054
There's no glossing over
the suicide of their father.

924
01:07:52,132 --> 01:07:54,760
And there's
no sugarcoating this fact:

925
01:07:54,835 --> 01:07:58,703
My client is guilty,
and he deserves to be punished.

926
01:08:01,107 --> 01:08:04,440
Mens rea: to do the thing.

927
01:08:04,511 --> 01:08:06,775
Sam Cayhall did the thing.

928
01:08:06,847 --> 01:08:09,111
But he does not deserve
to be murdered,

929
01:08:09,182 --> 01:08:12,242
because he was taught
from birth that he had to do the thing.

930
01:08:12,319 --> 01:08:15,288
That is what this court
must come to understand.

931
01:08:15,355 --> 01:08:17,380
He never knew he had
any other recourse...

932
01:08:17,457 --> 01:08:20,392
but hatred and bigotry
and violence.

933
01:08:20,460 --> 01:08:25,397
His uncles were Klansmen, his brothers,
his father, even his grandfather.

934
01:08:25,465 --> 01:08:29,731
His great-grandfather was
one of the cofounding members
of that hateful organization.

935
01:08:29,803 --> 01:08:33,569
I recently saw a photograph
of him a-at a lynching.

936
01:08:33,640 --> 01:08:36,507
He was ten,
and it was his third.

937
01:08:38,144 --> 01:08:41,136
Of course this is awful.
It... It's evil.

938
01:08:41,214 --> 01:08:44,581
But blood and death were served
with Sunday breakfast.

939
01:08:46,086 --> 01:08:49,522
His father was murdered at a funeral.
My client saw it.

940
01:08:52,058 --> 01:08:55,892
As the court is no doubt aware,
my client is also my grandfather.

941
01:08:55,962 --> 01:09:00,558
I'd like now to tell you some warm
and wonderful stories about our family.

942
01:09:00,634 --> 01:09:02,568
Except I don't know any.

943
01:09:04,070 --> 01:09:08,530
In fact, I don't find
my grandfather even remotely wonderful.

944
01:09:09,743 --> 01:09:11,768
But I know this.

945
01:09:11,845 --> 01:09:14,109
The very things that
make him so monstrous...

946
01:09:14,180 --> 01:09:17,547
are the very reasons that mitigate
against this state murdering him.

947
01:09:17,617 --> 01:09:20,347
He was raised by his family
and by this state...

948
01:09:20,420 --> 01:09:22,718
to become the man that he became.

949
01:09:22,789 --> 01:09:25,451
By the time he was old enough
to choose, he didn't have a choice.

950
01:09:26,993 --> 01:09:28,927
This is the tragedy of Sam Cayhall.

951
01:09:31,398 --> 01:09:35,892
It's a tragedy that has
destroyed three lives already.

952
01:09:37,604 --> 01:09:40,368
In the name of mercy,

953
01:09:40,440 --> 01:09:44,536
let it not murder what little
is left of his life.

954
01:10:01,661 --> 01:10:04,459
[Sighs]
Thank you for seeing me like this.

955
01:10:04,531 --> 01:10:07,364
Why are you here?

956
01:10:09,169 --> 01:10:13,162
I'm hoping you'll ask the governor
to show some mercy.

957
01:10:13,239 --> 01:10:15,673
Tell him that you don't want
my client to die.

958
01:10:15,742 --> 01:10:18,040
I don't want him to die.

959
01:10:18,111 --> 01:10:21,740
I don't want him to.
But I feel he must.

960
01:10:21,815 --> 01:10:24,545
See, that's...
that's not true. It isn't.

961
01:10:24,617 --> 01:10:27,415
Your word would carry a lot
of weight with the governor,

962
01:10:27,487 --> 01:10:30,888
and no one knows more than you that
there's already been enough suffering.

963
01:10:30,957 --> 01:10:33,858
It could all end right here.
Right now.

964
01:10:36,229 --> 01:10:40,996
I didn't take them to nursery school
that mornin' because I was sick.

965
01:10:41,067 --> 01:10:45,094
So I waved good-bye
from my bedroom window...

966
01:10:45,171 --> 01:10:48,334
and watched them leapfrog off
to their death.

967
01:10:48,408 --> 01:10:50,899
Bye, Mommy! I love you!

968
01:10:50,977 --> 01:10:53,070
[Mrs. Kramer]
The whole thing was my fault.

969
01:10:53,146 --> 01:10:55,512
Be good!

970
01:10:57,751 --> 01:11:00,413
- Adam.
- Ma'am?

971
01:11:00,487 --> 01:11:03,081
Why are you really here?

972
01:11:12,032 --> 01:11:17,197
I came home one day and found my father
on the floor with a gun in his hand.

973
01:11:17,270 --> 01:11:21,604
And I remember wondering,
What are all those towels doing there?

974
01:11:23,443 --> 01:11:28,210
And then I realized that he had arranged
the towels in a circle...

975
01:11:28,281 --> 01:11:31,250
and then very carefully...

976
01:11:31,317 --> 01:11:34,309
laid down in the center of them
so that he wouldn't make a mess.

977
01:11:36,523 --> 01:11:39,720
In his note, he... he said
that he loved me.

978
01:11:39,793 --> 01:11:42,956
And he was sorry, and...

979
01:11:43,029 --> 01:11:45,259
he hoped that
one day I'd understand.

980
01:11:45,331 --> 01:11:49,267
He told me I'd have to take care
of Mom and my sister.

981
01:11:51,137 --> 01:11:54,163
There was a plastic garbage bag
on the floor next to him.

982
01:11:54,240 --> 01:11:58,574
I was supposed to put the towels
in the bag, clean up the mess
and call the police.

983
01:11:58,645 --> 01:12:01,136
Don't touch the gun,
he said.

984
01:12:01,214 --> 01:12:03,375
Hurry up before the girls get home.

985
01:12:04,951 --> 01:12:08,614
See, he had picked a day
when he knew I'd be the first one home.

986
01:12:10,490 --> 01:12:12,424
I was ten.

987
01:12:13,526 --> 01:12:16,461
I would dearly love
to help you, Adam.

988
01:12:16,529 --> 01:12:19,396
Please know this.

989
01:12:19,466 --> 01:12:21,764
Sam Cayhall destroyed
both our families.

990
01:12:21,835 --> 01:12:24,827
Mine just died first.

991
01:12:24,904 --> 01:12:28,601
And I'm sorry...
but he has to die.

992
01:12:28,675 --> 01:12:31,667
Why?

993
01:12:31,744 --> 01:12:36,681
He has to die because I had champagne
at my birthday party.

994
01:12:36,749 --> 01:12:40,515
He has to die
because a story needs an ending.

995
01:12:42,822 --> 01:12:47,555
He has to die because...
I don't care if he had no choice.

996
01:12:47,627 --> 01:12:51,063
He chose to bomb that building.

997
01:12:51,131 --> 01:12:53,065
And my family died.

998
01:12:59,672 --> 01:13:01,606
You know,
they were your age then.

999
01:13:04,277 --> 01:13:08,338
Mmm. And they would've been
your age now.

1000
01:13:41,848 --> 01:13:44,112
[F.B.I. Man]
Haven't given up, have you?

1001
01:13:44,184 --> 01:13:46,914
[Laughing]

1002
01:13:46,986 --> 01:13:51,013
Sometimes l... I just like to see
if I still have what it takes.

1003
01:13:51,090 --> 01:13:55,186
- Jesus. What are you doing here?
- I've been watching you, kid.

1004
01:13:55,261 --> 01:13:57,195
You deserve the facts.

1005
01:13:58,831 --> 01:14:03,734
Back in '67, I found an old drunk.
He was a dish washer.

1006
01:14:03,803 --> 01:14:08,467
Claimed the night
before the Kramer bombing,
he saw Sam in a diner with another guy.

1007
01:14:08,541 --> 01:14:11,237
I need a name.

1008
01:14:11,311 --> 01:14:14,747
The description matched a guy
we always suspected, but...

1009
01:14:14,814 --> 01:14:17,647
R.W.

1010
01:14:17,717 --> 01:14:20,117
Hey! Rollie Wedge.

1011
01:14:24,557 --> 01:14:28,459
He was a real hater. But smart.
And we could never tie him to anything.

1012
01:14:28,528 --> 01:14:31,361
- Where is he now?
- They've gathered.

1013
01:14:31,431 --> 01:14:33,365
You know, sort of like a reunion.

1014
01:14:33,433 --> 01:14:36,630
The night before the big execution
and all that.

1015
01:14:36,703 --> 01:14:39,872
I figure, if he's here,
he's there.

1016
01:15:10,435 --> 01:15:13,097
[Man #1] Slapped the hell out of him.

1017
01:15:13,171 --> 01:15:15,469
[Man #2] Nigger lover.

1018
01:15:15,540 --> 01:15:17,474
[Man #3]
Don't let the gore hit you, handsome.

1019
01:15:17,542 --> 01:15:21,103
- Hey!
- [Man #3] He wasn't able to make it.

1020
01:15:21,179 --> 01:15:25,115
[Men Chattering, Laughing]

1021
01:15:37,529 --> 01:15:41,226
[Men Arguing, Chattering Loudly]

1022
01:15:54,746 --> 01:15:57,078
[Cheering, Shouting]

1023
01:15:59,818 --> 01:16:01,877
[Grunting]

1024
01:16:18,570 --> 01:16:22,062
[Shouting, Cheering Continue]

1025
01:16:24,242 --> 01:16:26,710
[Skinhead] Come on.
Get him outta here.

1026
01:16:33,085 --> 01:16:35,986
- Let's go, fucker! Get outta here!
- Yeah!

1027
01:16:36,054 --> 01:16:38,545
- Yeah!
- [Adam Moaning]

1028
01:16:40,425 --> 01:16:43,258
Get away from that boy.

1029
01:16:43,328 --> 01:16:45,387
Let's git!

1030
01:16:47,099 --> 01:16:50,364
[Adam Moaning, Panting]
Oh, God. Oh, God.

1031
01:16:50,435 --> 01:16:53,268
Thank you. [Panting]

1032
01:16:53,338 --> 01:16:55,272
I appreciate it.

1033
01:16:55,340 --> 01:16:57,706
- [Gun Cocks]
- You do?

1034
01:17:01,880 --> 01:17:03,814
[Panting]

1035
01:17:05,350 --> 01:17:08,581
- Rollie Wedge.
- One of the many names I've been called.

1036
01:17:08,653 --> 01:17:12,316
What do you think
you're doin' here?

1037
01:17:12,391 --> 01:17:14,325
You planted the bomb
that killed those kids.

1038
01:17:14,393 --> 01:17:18,090
Were you plannin'
a citizen's arrest?

1039
01:17:18,163 --> 01:17:20,631
- [Skinheads Laugh]
- I just want to hear you admit it.

1040
01:17:20,699 --> 01:17:25,068
Delusion, Mr. Hall.
You're lookin' for a clean yes,

1041
01:17:25,137 --> 01:17:28,231
so you can identify, quantify,

1042
01:17:28,306 --> 01:17:30,740
organize the concept of evil.

1043
01:17:30,809 --> 01:17:33,778
If I did it,
then I'm the evil,

1044
01:17:33,845 --> 01:17:36,780
and I can be culled
from the flock.

1045
01:17:36,848 --> 01:17:39,817
Removed, separated, destroyed.

1046
01:17:39,885 --> 01:17:42,046
Evil can be destroyed.

1047
01:17:42,120 --> 01:17:44,816
And all you good people
can feel safe...

1048
01:17:44,890 --> 01:17:47,950
in the cocoon of your denial.

1049
01:17:48,026 --> 01:17:51,120
- Sam says you're his people.
- We are one.

1050
01:17:51,196 --> 01:17:53,528
Oh, is this how you treat your people?

1051
01:17:53,598 --> 01:17:56,032
Huh? Let them take the fall for you?

1052
01:17:57,936 --> 01:18:01,804
What about loyalty?
Huh? What about the truth?

1053
01:18:04,042 --> 01:18:06,272
[Gunshot]

1054
01:18:08,513 --> 01:18:12,643
The truth, based on your laws,
Attorney Hall,

1055
01:18:12,717 --> 01:18:17,086
is that Sam Cayhall is guilty
and has been sentenced to death.

1056
01:18:17,155 --> 01:18:20,181
Perhaps it's time
for you to show some loyalty,

1057
01:18:20,258 --> 01:18:22,886
and let justice be served.

1058
01:18:22,961 --> 01:18:26,294
And after it is,

1059
01:18:26,364 --> 01:18:29,959
always look behind ya.

1060
01:18:30,035 --> 01:18:31,969
Always.

1061
01:18:36,875 --> 01:18:38,809
[Skinhead Laughing]

1062
01:18:45,884 --> 01:18:48,182
- [Adam] He's probably still there.
- Uh-huh.

1063
01:18:49,621 --> 01:18:52,055
- And?
- If Sam were being tried
as an accomplice,

1064
01:18:52,124 --> 01:18:54,058
the most he would get
is 20 years.

1065
01:18:54,126 --> 01:18:57,618
- Now, you said
you wanted new information.
- With all due respect,

1066
01:18:57,696 --> 01:19:01,632
this is hardly compelling
evidence of anything.

1067
01:19:01,700 --> 01:19:03,668
Grant a stay.
Give me more time.

1068
01:19:06,204 --> 01:19:09,469
[Man] All right, men.
Listen up. It's now 0800 hours.

1069
01:19:09,541 --> 01:19:12,510
I'm hereby activating
the emergency operations center...

1070
01:19:12,577 --> 01:19:14,772
and placing this institution
on lockdown status.

1071
01:19:14,846 --> 01:19:18,577
And I expect each of you
to discharge your duty accordingly.

1072
01:19:18,650 --> 01:19:21,517
No second-guessing,
no improvisin'.

1073
01:19:21,586 --> 01:19:24,680
This execution will take place
in 16 hours.

1074
01:19:39,271 --> 01:19:41,205
[Exhales]

1075
01:19:42,707 --> 01:19:46,370
- [Exhales]
- [Heavy Door Opening]

1076
01:20:23,682 --> 01:20:26,651
What you did to those babies...

1077
01:20:28,720 --> 01:20:31,655
no one could ever forgive you for.

1078
01:20:34,159 --> 01:20:37,219
What you did to me...

1079
01:20:38,296 --> 01:20:40,628
and Eddie,

1080
01:20:42,667 --> 01:20:45,636
I've got to.

1081
01:20:55,080 --> 01:20:57,014
Not for you, old man.

1082
01:21:01,186 --> 01:21:03,120
For me.

1083
01:21:23,608 --> 01:21:27,009
[Crying] Eddie said...

1084
01:21:28,079 --> 01:21:32,277
you'd never have shot Joe Lincoln,

1085
01:21:33,418 --> 01:21:38,412
if I'd have cried out
for you not to.

1086
01:21:38,490 --> 01:21:40,424
Is that why you came here?

1087
01:21:45,163 --> 01:21:47,097
No.

1088
01:21:55,140 --> 01:21:57,074
Would you still have shot him?

1089
01:22:01,613 --> 01:22:04,173
Yeah. Yeah.

1090
01:22:28,506 --> 01:22:32,135
- [Sobs]
- [Door Closing]

1091
01:22:32,210 --> 01:22:36,874
[TV Announcer] The fifth circuit
court denied Sam Cayhall's last appeal.

1092
01:22:36,948 --> 01:22:39,917
The U.S. Supreme Court will rule
later today on his fate.

1093
01:22:39,984 --> 01:22:44,421
If they deny, Governor David McAllister
will be his last chance.

1094
01:22:44,489 --> 01:22:48,393
The execution is set
for 12:01 tomorrow morning.

1095
01:22:48,726 --> 01:22:50,853
Stephanie Bell Flint,
WLBT News.

1096
01:22:53,331 --> 01:22:55,765
[Gate Unlocking, Sliding]

1097
01:22:56,934 --> 01:22:59,300
[Inmate Whistles]
You got a light, yeah?

1098
01:23:01,406 --> 01:23:04,534
[Gate Unlocking, Sliding]

1099
01:23:16,754 --> 01:23:18,745
Sam.

1100
01:23:21,893 --> 01:23:24,828
Met some of your real people
last night.

1101
01:23:26,631 --> 01:23:30,658
Real interesting group.
They're real people.

1102
01:23:33,237 --> 01:23:35,171
Especially Rollie Wedge.

1103
01:23:37,475 --> 01:23:40,137
Rollie... Wedge.

1104
01:23:42,013 --> 01:23:44,004
He was real interesting.

1105
01:24:02,233 --> 01:24:04,167
I have to talk to the guards.

1106
01:24:04,235 --> 01:24:06,169
[Guard] Rack up, Sam.

1107
01:24:11,742 --> 01:24:14,802
[Footsteps Retreating]

1108
01:24:16,414 --> 01:24:19,144
You look a lot
like your brother, Mr. Cayhall.

1109
01:24:53,351 --> 01:24:56,184
I came to pay
my respects, Sam.

1110
01:24:58,122 --> 01:25:00,056
Say good-bye.

1111
01:25:00,124 --> 01:25:03,525
Make sure you're still strong.

1112
01:25:09,634 --> 01:25:11,727
I saw those two little kids.

1113
01:25:13,538 --> 01:25:16,132
They was in the window.

1114
01:25:17,208 --> 01:25:19,904
That was a mistake.

1115
01:25:19,977 --> 01:25:22,070
We kept two little Jews...

1116
01:25:22,146 --> 01:25:25,309
from growin' up into big Jews.

1117
01:25:25,383 --> 01:25:27,442
When their nigger-lovin' father
killed hisself,

1118
01:25:27,518 --> 01:25:31,147
it was like droppin' a little
hook-nosed pebble in a pond.

1119
01:25:33,090 --> 01:25:37,424
The ripples went out with a message
for all the world to see.

1120
01:25:38,496 --> 01:25:41,363
A Jew is weak.

1121
01:25:42,433 --> 01:25:45,197
How do you figure that
for a mistake?

1122
01:25:45,269 --> 01:25:47,464
Wasn't supposed to be
no killin'.

1123
01:25:47,538 --> 01:25:50,063
Don't go soft, Sam.

1124
01:25:50,141 --> 01:25:52,075
The day is comin'.

1125
01:25:55,246 --> 01:25:59,410
I wish you could stick around
to see it, buddy. It's comin'.

1126
01:25:59,483 --> 01:26:02,646
Every day more and more people
are openin' their eyes...

1127
01:26:02,720 --> 01:26:04,847
to see the only thing wrong
with this country...

1128
01:26:04,922 --> 01:26:08,153
is we've gone against
the laws of nature.

1129
01:26:08,225 --> 01:26:10,159
God's law.

1130
01:26:12,630 --> 01:26:17,033
Only the strong have
a right to survive.

1131
01:26:17,101 --> 01:26:20,468
And now, finally,

1132
01:26:20,538 --> 01:26:22,472
those not worthy...

1133
01:26:22,540 --> 01:26:26,135
the Jew, the African,

1134
01:26:26,210 --> 01:26:28,144
he who lies with another man...

1135
01:26:28,212 --> 01:26:30,806
they're all diggin' their own graves.

1136
01:26:30,881 --> 01:26:35,818
And when we pile 'em in there,
I'll drink a toast to you, Sam.

1137
01:26:35,886 --> 01:26:38,980
And I'll piss it out
on their dead faces.

1138
01:26:39,056 --> 01:26:40,990
No.

1139
01:26:41,058 --> 01:26:43,822
You've been a good
and loyal soldier, Sam.

1140
01:26:43,894 --> 01:26:46,761
Go with the dignity
that is yours.

1141
01:26:46,831 --> 01:26:49,629
Don't be confused
by that little boy!

1142
01:26:49,700 --> 01:26:52,828
He's got his daddy's
weak blood in him.

1143
01:26:52,903 --> 01:26:55,872
He ain't pure.
He ain't us.

1144
01:26:55,940 --> 01:27:00,343
No. You son of a bitch, you.
You son of a bitch.

1145
01:27:01,412 --> 01:27:04,848
I ain't you. I ain't you!

1146
01:27:04,915 --> 01:27:08,578
You touch my kid,
and I'm gonna kill you!

1147
01:27:08,653 --> 01:27:12,521
- [Guards Shouting]
- Rip your head off! I'll kill you,
you goddamn son of a bitch.

1148
01:27:12,590 --> 01:27:14,387
- You know who this is?
- [Guard] Your brother.

1149
01:27:14,458 --> 01:27:17,894
Oh, no, he ain't my brother!
You ain't my brother!

1150
01:27:17,962 --> 01:27:20,396
- Better get outta here.
- I'll be prayin' for ya, Sam.

1151
01:27:20,464 --> 01:27:25,231
- You got to hell, you son
of a bitch, you! Go to hell!
- I'll be prayin' for ya.

1152
01:27:25,302 --> 01:27:28,237
[Demonstrators Shouting]

1153
01:27:38,649 --> 01:27:42,016
[Packer] Rack, Sam.

1154
01:27:44,989 --> 01:27:46,923
No word from the courts.

1155
01:28:02,506 --> 01:28:05,771
I'd like you to mail
these for me, if you would.

1156
01:28:08,612 --> 01:28:11,308
I don't have the addresses.

1157
01:28:25,129 --> 01:28:27,063
Don't give up, Sam.

1158
01:28:27,131 --> 01:28:29,065
Mmm.

1159
01:28:32,670 --> 01:28:34,604
There is one other thing.

1160
01:28:46,083 --> 01:28:48,017
Take that.

1161
01:28:53,591 --> 01:28:55,525
[Packer] Rack, Sam.

1162
01:28:59,897 --> 01:29:01,831
[Pager Beeping]

1163
01:29:04,034 --> 01:29:06,002
[Adam] It's the Supreme Court.

1164
01:29:06,070 --> 01:29:08,334
Coffee's French Market,
just like you asked.

1165
01:29:08,405 --> 01:29:10,339
Thank you.

1166
01:29:14,578 --> 01:29:16,512
Rack back.

1167
01:29:22,086 --> 01:29:24,281
Adam Hall.

1168
01:29:30,294 --> 01:29:32,228
Mmm.

1169
01:29:43,374 --> 01:29:45,342
It ain't over, Sam.

1170
01:29:45,409 --> 01:29:47,468
It ain't over.

1171
01:29:47,545 --> 01:29:49,979
- [Footsteps, Running]
- [Wrapper Tearing]

1172
01:29:52,216 --> 01:29:54,150
